%section
  %h1 Advanced selectors

%section
  .codepen(data-height="450" data-editable="true" data-theme-id="0" data-slug-hash="OJLgPMM" data-default-tab="css,result" data-user="htmlboy")
  %p.note
    The child selector (<code>&gt;</code>) only applies to a direct descendant
    (rather than nested ones). The <code>+</code> selector refers to the adjacent
    element below.

%section
  .codepen(data-height="400" data-editable="true" data-theme-id="0" data-slug-hash="OJLgLmQ" data-default-tab="css,result" data-user="htmlboy")
  %p.note
    The pseudo-classes <code>:first-child</code> and <code>:last-child</code>
    refer to the position that an element occupies (if it is first or last) in a
    context (or HTML node).


%section
  .codepen(data-height="400" data-editable="true" data-theme-id="0" data-slug-hash="VwZWwwQ" data-default-tab="css,result" data-user="htmlboy")
  %p.note
    With the pseudo-class <code>:nth-child()</code> we can apply styles to
    elements in a specific position. We refer to the element in a position by giving
    a number (argument) inside the parentheses. If we add an <code>n</code>, we
    indicate repetition, and adding or subtracting a number will modify the point
    at which it begins to count.

%section
  .codepen(data-height="400" data-editable="true" data-theme-id="0" data-slug-hash="xxKrxRL" data-default-tab="css,result" data-user="htmlboy")
  %p.note
    With <code>:first-of-type</code>, <code>:last-of-type</code> or
    <code>:nth-of-type()</code> we can refer to the position of an element
    according to its type of HTML tag.

%section
  .codepen(data-height="400" data-editable="true" data-theme-id="0" data-slug-hash="xxKrbdm" data-default-tab="css,result" data-user="htmlboy")
  %p.note
    The <code>[]</code> attribute selector can be applied to an element that has
    an attribute or which attribute is equal to a certain value.


%section
  .codepen(data-height="400" data-editable="true" data-theme-id="0" data-slug-hash="vYBZEyB" data-default-tab="css,result" data-user="htmlboy")
  %p.note
    The <code>:not()</code> selector applies an exception to the rule (a class,
    an attributeâ€¦). It does not allow combinations of parameters.

%section
  .codepen(data-height="400" data-editable="true" data-theme-id="0" data-slug-hash="ExYXvbd" data-default-tab="css,result" data-user="htmlboy")
  %p.note
    The pseudo-elements <code>::before</code> and <code>::after</code> allow us
    to add content at the beginning and end of an HTML tag, providing this tag can
    have contents (they do not work with <code>&lt;img&gt;</code>, for example).

%section
  .codepen(data-height="400" data-editable="true" data-theme-id="0" data-slug-hash="oNvweav" data-default-tab="css,result" data-user="htmlboy")
  %p.note
    The pseudo-element <code>::first-line</code> allows us to apply styles to the
    first line of a block of text. <code>::first-letter</code> applies styles to
    the first letter, and <code>::selection</code> to the selected text.

